[{"short_id":"imwkxe","created_at":"2026-03-10T16:41:15.000-05:00","title":"Unions merged into dotnet 11 preview 3","url":"https://github.com/dotnet/csharplang/blob/main/proposals/unions.md","score":2,"flags":0,"comment_count":1,"description":"\u003cp\u003eStruggling to find a link that lobsters allows. But unions have been merged into dotnet 11:\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eJulien Couvreur (@jcouv)\nWe merged an early C# 15 preview feature into .NET 11 preview 3: unions.\u003c/p\u003e\n\u003cp\u003eAdds union declarations (\u003ccode\u003eunion Pet(Cat, Dog, Bird) { ... }\u003c/code\u003e) and union types (attributed with \u003ccode\u003e[Union]\u003c/code\u003e).\nThey can be treated by pattern matching/switch expressions as a closed set for exhaustiveness.\u003c/p\u003e\n","description_plain":"Struggling to find a link that lobsters allows. But unions have been merged into dotnet 11:\r\n\r\nJulien Couvreur (@jcouv)\r\nWe merged an early C# 15 preview feature into .NET 11 preview 3: unions.\r\n\r\nAdds union declarations (`union Pet(Cat, Dog, Bird) { ... }`) and union types (attributed with `[Union]`).\r\nThey can be treated by pattern matching/switch expressions as a closed set for exhaustiveness.","submitter_user":"martinald","user_is_author":false,"tags":["dotnet"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/imwkxe","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/imwkxe/unions_merged_into_dotnet_11_preview_3"},{"short_id":"2fzuf8","created_at":"2026-03-10T16:33:25.000-05:00","title":"TLA+ as a Design Accelerator: Lessons from the Industry","url":"http://muratbuffalo.blogspot.com/2026/03/tla-as-design-accelerator-lessons-from.html","score":1,"flags":0,"comment_count":0,"description":"","description_plain":"","submitter_user":"eatonphil","user_is_author":false,"tags":["databases","formalmethods"],"short_id_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2fzuf8","comments_url":"https://lobste.rs/s/2fzuf8/tla_as_design_accelerator_lessons_from"},{"short_id":"wvewpi","created_at":"2026-03-10T16:12:44.000-05: